00:23:24.990 --> 00:23:26.816
&gt;&gt; At the dawn of the atomic age
some people thought the genie could

00:23:27.630 --> 00:23:28.176
be stopped and others thought it was
inevitable, just a matter of time.

00:23:31.750 --> 00:23:34.283
Do you think it could
have been stopped

00:23:34.830 --> 00:23:38.896
and what do you think people
will think another 100 years out?

00:23:39.820 --> 00:23:43.620
How do you think this will
evolve that thinking over time?

00:23:43.930 --> 00:23:44.716
&gt;&gt; Could they have kept the
genie pushed down in the bottle

00:23:47.010 --> 00:23:50.476
or was the development of
nuclear weapons inevitable?

00:23:50.690 --> 00:23:54.823
You know, I always quote something
Robert Oppenheimer once said

00:23:54.970 --> 00:23:55.073
that I think speaks
exactly to this question.

00:23:57.800 --> 00:24:00.933
He said the deep things
in science are not found

00:24:01.070 --> 00:24:02.670
because they are useful.

00:24:03.540 --> 00:24:07.006
They were found because it
was possible to find them.

00:24:08.240 --> 00:24:11.906
Nuclear fission was an
inevitable outcome of the studies

00:24:11.990 --> 00:24:13.170
of the nucleus of the atom
of the atom that began

00:24:14.010 --> 00:24:16.543
in the early years
of the 20th century.

00:24:16.620 --> 00:24:20.953
You reach a certain point and you
inevitably find nuclear fission.

00:24:21.940 --> 00:24:22.073
Once nuclear fission was found--

00:24:23.940 --> 00:24:25.150
and I say inevitable because
scientists all over the world

00:24:26.530 --> 00:24:26.953
when they got the word that
2 German radio chemists

00:24:29.440 --> 00:24:33.106
that identified this amazing
new reaction scientists all

00:24:33.190 --> 00:24:33.390
over the world kicked themselves.

00:24:35.190 --> 00:24:35.893
They understood that they've
been seeing it in their labs

00:24:38.220 --> 00:24:39.293
but because they hadn't
thought through what was going

00:24:40.680 --> 00:24:43.146
on they hadn't identified
what it was.

00:24:43.750 --> 00:24:45.253
And I mean really, I've talked to
a number of them who were just sick

00:24:46.780 --> 00:24:50.380
for a couple of days after
this huge discovery was made

00:24:50.510 --> 00:24:51.636
that they missed just because
they didn't think it through.

00:24:53.250 --> 00:24:57.516
So, it inevitably came along and
the idea that this was some sort

00:24:57.920 --> 00:24:58.653
of falsity and bargain on
the part of the scientist

00:25:00.520 --> 00:25:01.936
that they all could have
gone off in a room somewhere

00:25:02.570 --> 00:25:02.750
up in a mountain top and said, oh
let's not do this, is simply absurd.

00:25:06.990 --> 00:25:11.723
There it was and the reaction was so
fiercely exothermic, so much energy

00:25:12.190 --> 00:25:14.056
out for so little energy in.

00:25:14.490 --> 00:25:15.366
And in the context of the discovery
having been made nine months before

00:25:18.280 --> 00:25:18.680
the beginning of the
Second World War

00:25:20.280 --> 00:25:20.983
in Europe inevitably people would
think of the possibility of a bomb.

00:25:24.110 --> 00:25:25.910
Now what followed from that

00:25:26.190 --> 00:25:30.656
and the nuclear arms raise those
inevitably were political decisions

00:25:31.080 --> 00:25:31.186
made for many different
kinds of reasons.

00:25:33.640 --> 00:25:37.906
I think fundamentally, at least
at the beginning, from deep fears

00:25:37.930 --> 00:25:40.730
that the only defense
against these weapons

00:25:40.730 --> 00:25:41.330
which the scientists
recognized as early

00:25:42.730 --> 00:25:46.863
as 1939 would be similar arsenal
and the threat of retaliation.

00:25:48.430 --> 00:25:50.763
That kept it going for a long time.

00:25:51.000 --> 00:25:54.200
So I think that's a full
answer to that question.

00:25:55.480 --> 00:25:56.480
Yes?

00:25:57.480 --> 00:25:58.170
&gt;&gt; Yes. A lot of people don't
know there was this genius--

00:26:00.590 --> 00:26:02.856
genius, genius in Meredith Gardner

00:26:03.150 --> 00:26:07.216
and he broke the indecipherable
ciphers that the Soviet's used

00:26:10.660 --> 00:26:11.193
and this is called
the VENONA messages.

00:26:12.660 --> 00:26:13.793
&gt;&gt; Oh yes, right.

00:26:14.660 --> 00:26:17.993
&gt;&gt; Into 30s and to 40s and
he broke them in the 50s

00:26:18.420 --> 00:26:22.486
and if you read the VENONA
messages I think you will find some

00:26:22.580 --> 00:26:26.180
justification as to why we
have atomic bombs [laughter]

00:26:27.150 --> 00:26:31.150
but the second thing is in the
VENONA messages I always knew,

00:26:32.950 --> 00:26:33.136
every one that knew that
[inaudible], green glass,

00:26:36.030 --> 00:26:37.830
definitely as the Rosenberg

00:26:38.030 --> 00:26:42.096
and Julia state they didn't have
access to the atomic secrets.

00:26:42.740 --> 00:26:47.206
A man that did that was messaged--
a young American called Ted Hall,

00:26:47.760 --> 00:26:52.160
Theodore Hall and yet he immigrated
to the United States-- England.

00:26:53.250 --> 00:26:54.583
&gt;&gt; In England, yeah.

00:26:55.250 --> 00:26:56.650
&gt;&gt; He was a Cambridge
professor and he died old age.

00:26:57.250 --> 00:26:57.716
He was never put to
death or anything.

00:26:59.250 --> 00:27:00.250
&gt;&gt; Right.

00:27:01.250 --> 00:27:02.783
&gt;&gt; And he gave the Soviets
most of the usable secrets.

00:27:03.250 --> 00:27:04.450
&gt;&gt; That's correct.

00:27:05.250 --> 00:27:06.316
&gt;&gt; Can you comment on
both of those two things?

00:27:07.250 --> 00:27:09.050
&gt;&gt; Yeah, I think, you know,

00:27:09.250 --> 00:27:11.783
it's always puzzled me why Ted Hall
was allowed to live out his life.

00:27:11.250 --> 00:27:12.220
I think that suggest that he had new
things or had documents or something

00:27:15.080 --> 00:27:19.280
that our government security
people didn't want to see released,

00:27:19.530 --> 00:27:22.196
that's usually why
people aren't touched.

00:27:22.340 --> 00:27:26.540
But the larger question, I'll
just speak to it with an anecdote,

00:27:26.930 --> 00:27:31.130
could the Soviets have build an
atomic bomb within the timeframe

00:27:31.760 --> 00:27:35.960
that they did about the same time
it took us without the secrets

00:27:36.590 --> 00:27:36.710
that were passed to
them by their spies?

00:27:39.070 --> 00:27:43.403
And I corresponded with this Soviet
Robert Oppenheimer a man named

00:27:45.470 --> 00:27:46.136
[inaudible] in the
last years of his life

00:27:47.470 --> 00:27:50.536
by the new thing e-mail
back in the early '90s.

00:27:50.940 --> 00:27:55.206
And he pointed out that by 1947
they had worked out a bomb design

00:27:55.630 --> 00:27:59.696
that would be half as heavy,
half as big and twice as powerful

00:28:00.030 --> 00:28:02.563
as our first bomb as
our Nagasaki bomb.

00:28:03.590 --> 00:28:05.590
And I said why didn't you do--

00:28:05.590 --> 00:28:06.066
build that one instead of
building a copy of ours?

00:28:08.380 --> 00:28:11.980
And he said because Lavrentiy
Beria who was the monster

00:28:12.510 --> 00:28:15.576
who ran the Gulag system
and was also in charge

00:28:16.090 --> 00:28:19.956
of their bomb program had said
to them with great contempt,

00:28:20.120 --> 00:28:23.786
I don't give a damn what you
think is a workable design.

00:28:24.230 --> 00:28:27.030
Build me the American
bomb I know it works.

00:28:28.670 --> 00:28:30.670
He said it was worth our lives

00:28:31.000 --> 00:28:31.313
so we built the American bomb
that's what my government wanted.

00:28:34.820 --> 00:28:37.486
But then I noticed in
looking at the list

00:28:37.550 --> 00:28:41.483
of their tests their second
bomb test was of a bomb that was

00:28:41.900 --> 00:28:45.900
about half the size and twice
the yield of our Nagasaki bomb.

00:28:47.040 --> 00:28:48.706
So they built theirs next

00:28:49.040 --> 00:28:50.306
after they've fulfilled
the political requirements

00:28:51.040 --> 00:28:51.126
that were there for
them to deal with.

00:28:53.420 --> 00:28:54.420
Sir?

00:28:55.420 --> 00:28:57.666
&gt;&gt; Do you believe that Iran has any
interest in a nuclear power program

00:28:57.840 --> 00:29:00.906
or is it just solely a
nuclear weapons program?

00:29:00.910 --> 00:29:01.756
&gt;&gt; You know I think
there's-- I think it's--

00:29:02.930 --> 00:29:03.196
there's ample of reason to believe

00:29:04.930 --> 00:29:05.273
that Iran is following basically
the path that Israel followed.

00:29:08.720 --> 00:29:09.640
The sort of bomb in the basement not
acknowledged that we are building

00:29:12.400 --> 00:29:15.000
such a thing or have
built such a thing.

00:29:15.030 --> 00:29:17.696
It was a very successful
path for Israel,

00:29:17.940 --> 00:29:20.206
still is in many ways to this day.

00:29:20.820 --> 00:29:21.096
It leaves an ambiguity there
about their relationship

00:29:24.010 --> 00:29:25.676
to being a nuclear power,

00:29:26.010 --> 00:29:27.340
even though everyone knows
they are a nuclear power.

00:29:28.080 --> 00:29:30.546
So that seems to me
what Iran is doing

00:29:31.010 --> 00:29:31.110
but it's been progressing
very slowly

00:29:33.310 --> 00:29:34.006
which isn't just the
technological problems,

00:29:35.480 --> 00:29:35.653
although there are plenty of those.

00:29:37.640 --> 00:29:41.640
Arguably what they are doing is
as North Korea has been doing

00:29:42.650 --> 00:29:46.516
in a much more blatant way
trying to use their capabilities

00:29:46.940 --> 00:29:49.873
as a negotiating tool
to find some settlement

00:29:50.340 --> 00:29:52.740
with the United Stats in particular.

00:29:53.790 --> 00:29:53.966
North Korea, without question,
and you will read this

00:29:57.080 --> 00:29:57.136
in the books several chapters
may surprise you amazingly

00:30:00.690 --> 00:30:04.556
about North Korea's reasons
for developing nuclear weapons.

00:30:05.530 --> 00:30:09.996
&gt;&gt; Primarily it was because during
the Korean War we systematically,

00:30:10.760 --> 00:30:14.626
strategically bombed North
Korea back to the Stone Age just

00:30:14.780 --> 00:30:17.180
as Curtis LeMay had
threatened to do.

00:30:17.860 --> 00:30:22.126
We particularly destroyed all of
their hydroelectric dams as well

00:30:22.850 --> 00:30:27.650
as a lot of dams that controlled the
flood control for their rice fields.

00:30:27.700 --> 00:30:29.633
I mean it's a horrible story.

00:30:29.700 --> 00:30:30.373
We killed several million
North Korean civilians

00:30:32.160 --> 00:30:32.273
with strategic bombing
just as we had done

00:30:34.780 --> 00:30:35.376
against Japan during
the Second World War

00:30:36.850 --> 00:30:39.783
with perhaps more justification
in that case.

00:30:39.970 --> 00:30:43.503
Under those circumstances
the main goal of Kim Il-sung

00:30:45.160 --> 00:30:45.366
for many years thereafter was to get
an alliance with the United States

00:30:49.620 --> 00:30:51.486
that would allow North Korea

00:30:51.620 --> 00:30:51.813
to rebuild an electrical capacity
probably based on nuclear power.

00:30:55.760 --> 00:30:56.090
And it has been for that
purpose down through the years

00:30:59.030 --> 00:30:59.856
with other things thrown in
needless to say the presence

00:31:01.870 --> 00:31:02.080
of American nuclear weapons in South
Korea, the long standing conflict

00:31:06.260 --> 00:31:06.443
between North and South Korea
basically a long standing Civil War.

00:31:10.410 --> 00:31:10.883
All that's been there,
but underneath it all,

00:31:12.870 --> 00:31:13.336
and you'll hear it
every time you hear

00:31:14.870 --> 00:31:15.920
about what the North Koreans are
bringing to the negotiating table,

00:31:18.220 --> 00:31:18.286
they want an electrical supply.

00:31:20.220 --> 00:31:20.363
I mean, that's kind
of where we still are.

00:31:22.810 --> 00:31:23.516
When Bob Gallucci negotiated
the deal with them

00:31:25.170 --> 00:31:28.303
for two nuclear power
reactors of western design

00:31:28.790 --> 00:31:33.456
that the South Koreans would supply,
I said why did you give them that?

00:31:34.100 --> 00:31:34.233
He said that's what they wanted.

00:31:36.100 --> 00:31:36.716
And of course, they would be
under international control

00:31:39.150 --> 00:31:39.213
and all those things but-- so
it's not always what one reads

00:31:43.020 --> 00:31:43.370
in the papers that these are
crazy people and so forth.

